1
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:18,749
Shall I tell you a secret, Séverine?

2
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,870
I love you more every day.

3
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,592
And I you, Pierre.

4
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:27,154
You’re all I have, but —

5
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,793
But what?

6
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:34,670
I’d like everything to be perfect too.
If only you weren’t so cold.

7
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:36,831
Please don’t mention that again.

8
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:39,470
I didn’t mean to upset you.

9
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:41,990
I feel a great tenderness for you.

10
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:44,628
What good is your tenderness to me?

11
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:48,999
You can be very cruel
when you wish.

12
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:52,436
Forgive me, Pierre.

13
00:02:58,320 --> 00:02:59,799
Stop.

14
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:10,639
Get out.

15
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:13,558
- What’s going on?
- I said get out.

16
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:15,113
But why?

17
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:16,195
Come on.

18
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:19,596
- Let me go!
- Come on!

19
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:21,992
Let me go!

20
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:24,477
Do what I told you.

21
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:35,551
How dare you!

22
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,472
Let me go!

23
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:40,752
You brutes!

24
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:43,072
Let go of me!

25
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:48,474
It’s not my fault.
I can explain everything.

26
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:51,075
Go on.

27
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:54,192
Don’t worry about roughing up
the little slut! Hurry!

28
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:56,072
Pierre, it’s your fault too.

29
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:58,470
I can explain everything!

30
00:03:58,600 --> 00:04:01,956
Shut your mouth, madame,
or I’ll shut it for you!

31
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:11,239
Stop!

32
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:14,555
Please tell them to let me go!

33
00:04:20,280 --> 00:04:21,759
Help!

34
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:23,958
Shut up, you little bitch!

35
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,079
Come on.

36
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:34,993
Pull.

37
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:41,674
Don’t scream or I’ll kill you,
you hear?

38
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:44,430
Pierre, I beg you.

39
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:46,437
I beg your forgiveness

40
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:48,478
with all my heart.

41
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:06,518
Pierre, please don’t let the cats out!

42
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:26,031
That’s enough.
She’s yours now.

43
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:28,196
- Pierre, I love you!
- Go ahead.

44
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:39,511
What are you
Ihmkmg about, sever/he .7

45
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,956
What are you thinking about?

46
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:50,832
l was thinking about you... and us.

47
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:54,358
We were out for a ride in a carriage.

48
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:56,192
The carriage again?

49
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:05,518
I want to kiss you.

50
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:13,549
- You have an early day tomorrow.
- Why?

51
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:15,910
- To pack our bags.
- We’re going somewhere?

52
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:17,189
- Yes.
- Where?

53
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:19,954
It’s a surprise
for our wedding anniversary.

54
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:24,711
Our happiness has lasted a year already,
“and the suns of yesteryear...”

55
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:26,193
What about the hospital?

56
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:28,430
I want to forget about work
for a few days

57
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:30,471
and think only of you.

58
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:38,671
Happy?
- Yes.

59
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,472
Especially when you’re here.

60
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:43,239
I wish you could be
near me every second.

61
00:06:58,160 --> 00:06:59,798
No, please.

62
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:02,959
Sleep well.

63
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:07,393
Good night.

64
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:22,838
Forgive me.

65
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:27,229
You’re so good,
so understanding, but I —

66
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:29,755
It’s all right. Go to sleep.

67
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:43,395
You coming
to the party at the hotel?

68
00:07:43,520 --> 00:07:45,875
I don’t know.
Husson goes to bed at sundown.

69
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:49,629
Then come alone.
They say it’s going to snow tonight.

70
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:53,076
I’d love to see the mesmerizer.
I hear he’s great.

71
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,753
I won’t let him put me to sleep.

72
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:58,475
A mesmerizer isn’t a hypnotist.
He makes the sun rise.

73
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:01,791
A hypnotist plunges you
down into the depths.

74
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:04,560
Well, see you later.

75
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:06,398
Bye.

76
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:18,191
What time is it?

77
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:21,677
Five o’clock. You look bored.
Don’t let me keep you.

78
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,677
One’s never bored in a bar,

79
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:27,230
unlike in a church,
alone with one’s own soul.

80
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:30,720
l have something nice to tell you.

81
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:32,999
I love you.

82
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:34,679
Thank you.

83
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:36,916
Your scars heal so nicely.

84
00:08:37,040 --> 00:08:38,678
Oh, stop it.

85
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:48,198
Let’s not go in.
She’s with Husson.

86
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:49,833
Too late. He saw us.

87
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:52,838
What have you got against him?
He’s an interesting fellow.

88
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:55,394
I don’t like how he looks at me.

89
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:56,953
Come on.

90
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,358
Evening.

91
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:16,194
I saw you two
pass by earlier arm in arm.

92
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:19,198
It was a pleasure to see.
Like newlyweds.

93
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:22,630
- We must have looked ridiculous.
- No, it was very reassuring,

94
00:09:22,760 --> 00:09:25,228
like an everyday occurrence.

95
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:29,712
But you, Pierre — you sometimes
make me feel guilty and uneasy.

96
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:32,031
You and l are so different.

97
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:35,152
One really doesn’t meet
many men like you.

98
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:37,837
I mean it sincerely.

99
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:41,115
Well... thanks.

100
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:53,272
Another missed opportunity
for punishment.

101
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:55,755
Why? Do you know them?

102
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:57,712
Is that all you’re interested in?

103
00:09:57,840 --> 00:10:00,354
Everything else is useless.
A lot of wasted time.

104
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:03,756
You should see a specialist
about your obsessions.

105
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:07,395
He’s rich and idle.
Those are his two main illnesses.

106
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:09,273
Don’t forget the hunt.

107
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:12,915
I also have
a special weakness for the poor.

108
00:10:13,040 --> 00:10:16,635
I think of them when it snows,
with no fur coats, no hope, no nothing.

109
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:18,518
You’re very attractive, Séverine.

110
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:20,955
Your compliments are too subtle,
so just be quiet.

111
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:22,638
You’re asking the impossible.

112
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:26,156
I’ve been here three hours.
| feel a headache coming on.

113
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:28,430
It’s not too cold outside?
- No, it’s nice.

114
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:31,120
I’ll get some fresh air before dark.
See you later, Renee.

115
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:33,470
- See you later.
- Have a nice walk.

116
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:39,950
I like him. He’s amusing.

117
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:41,879
He’s strange.

118
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:43,712
Worse than that.

119
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:07,993
- / forgot to ask how Husson is.
- He’s fine.

120
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:10,998
- St/Y/ together?
- Afraid 50. Let’s not talk about it.

121
00:11:11,680 --> 00:11:14,274
You remember Henriette?
- Yes, very well.

122
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:16,912
It seems...

123
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:19,831
she’s turning tricks.

124
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:22,349
- What?
- In one of those houses.

125
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:24,875
They say she’s there
several days a week.

126
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:25,876
Well!

127
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:28,150
Can you believe it? Henriette!

128
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:31,759
Of course,
that’s all so far from your world.

129
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:35,671
But can you imagine?
A woman like you or me.

130
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:39,115
Can you see her
going with just anybody?

131
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:41,754
In those places
you don’t get to choose.

132
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:44,713
Old or not, lousy-looking or not.

133
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:49,194
Even with a man you love
it can be unpleasant.

134
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:53,233
It must be horrible with a stranger.
Those places still exist?

135
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:56,189
Excuse me, ladies,

136
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:59,830
but I can assure you:
Those places do still exist.

137
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:03,430
Oh, maybe not like
the joints before the war.

138
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:06,393
The red lights are gone, of course.

139
00:12:06,680 --> 00:12:09,797
But trust me:
There’s no lack of business.

140
00:12:10,280 --> 00:12:12,350
I could show you a good half dozen.

141
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:14,511
Part of my job, you see.

142
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:18,235
In 20 years of driving a cab
I’ve seen everything.

143
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:21,036
I’ve been mugged twice,

144
00:12:21,160 --> 00:12:23,310
and I’m none the worse for it.

145
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,391
Hey, what’s the matter?

146
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:30,079
We’re here.

147
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:06,796
These flowers came for you, madame.

148
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:08,951
Fine. Who sent them?

149
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:10,872
Mr. Husson.

150
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:21,471
Why did you put them here?

151
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:33,476
I’ll get a cloth.

152
00:13:33,760 --> 00:13:36,274
It’s nothing.
The water was clean.

153
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:07,196
What’s the matter with me today?

154
00:14:07,760 --> 00:14:09,591
saver/he, come quick/y!

155
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:17,390
Are you coming or not?

156
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:32,072
- Will you be much longer?
- I’m almost done.

157
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:47,795
Can I ask you a silly question?

158
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:49,473
Go ahead.

159
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:55,071
Before you met me,

160
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:58,272
did you use to go
to those... houses a lot?

161
00:14:58,880 --> 00:15:00,552
“Those houses”?

162
00:15:02,520 --> 00:15:06,069
Not very often. Why?
Does that interest you?

163
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:08,316
Everything about you interests me.

164
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:12,189
But I thought
they’d been closed down.

165
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:14,311
They’ve gone underground.

166
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:17,630
I can’t imagine how it works.

167
00:15:17,760 --> 00:15:20,593
- Listen, I have to work.
- Please.

168
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:26,391
Well, you go in.
The women are there.

169
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:28,398
You pick one.

170
00:15:28,520 --> 00:15:30,988
You spend half an hour
alone with her,

171
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:34,157
and after you leave,
you’re depressed all day.

172
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:37,829
But what can you do?
Semen retentum venenum est

173
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:39,473
Be quiet.

174
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:43,119
I don’t want to hear
any more, please.

175
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,638
What’s the matter?

176
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:52,789
I’ve never seen you like this.
What’s going on?

177
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:55,428
Nothing.
I’m just tired and on edge.

178
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:57,598
Go get some rest.

179
00:15:57,720 --> 00:15:59,199
You’re right.

180
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:01,913
Good night.

181
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:05,429
- Shall I come with you?
- No.

182
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:08,632
Yes, stay with me
until I fall asleep.

183
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:13,270
Will you never grow up?

184
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:36,035
I can’t hit anything today.
Take my place.

185
00:16:36,160 --> 00:16:38,993
- You leaving?
- No, I’ll wait for you inside.

186
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:51,750
- Hello, how are you?
- Not bad.

187
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:54,917
- We don’t see much of you these days.
- That’s true.

188
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:56,633
See you.

189
00:17:02,520 --> 00:17:04,829
The mysterious Henriette!

190
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:11,236
The woman with two faces.

191
00:17:11,880 --> 00:17:14,110
A double life. How intriguing!

192
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:18,156
Did Renée tell you?
- Yes. But why?

193
00:17:18,360 --> 00:17:20,351
Simple: for the money.

194
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:24,999
Most women who sell themselves
do so, alas, for the money.

195
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:32,630
It’s nice to see you, Séverine.
- I can’t understand women like that.

196
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:35,030
It’s the oldest profession
in the world.

197
00:17:35,240 --> 00:17:36,878
It’s mostly arranged by phone now,

198
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:39,793
but the women in those houses
are a special breed.

199
00:17:40,320 --> 00:17:42,151
I’m sure you know them well.

200
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:45,759
Yes, | used to go a lot.
I enjoyed it.

201
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:49,634
There’s a very special atmosphere.
The women are complete slaves.

202
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:52,389
I remember a few around the Opéra.

203
00:17:52,560 --> 00:17:55,120
Especially one run by Ana'is.

204
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:58,869
11, cité Jean de Saumur.
l have marvelous memories.

205
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:01,150
- Are you crazy?
- It’s nothing.

206
00:18:01,280 --> 00:18:03,874
A “cute compulsion,”
as the English say.

207
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:06,389
An insignificant little impulse.

208
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:08,915
I must see you sometime —

209
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:10,996
without your husband, of course.

210
00:18:11,120 --> 00:18:14,476
I admire Pierre very much,
but I’d prefer he not be there.

211
00:18:23,680 --> 00:18:27,150
Madame Anai's,
it, cite Jean de Saumur.

212
00:21:12,120 --> 00:21:13,599
Sévenne!

213
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:15,956
What’s the matter with you?

214
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:53,874
Yes?

215
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:56,474
- I wanted to speak to you.
- Come in.

216
00:21:58,640 --> 00:22:00,153
Good morning.

217
00:22:00,560 --> 00:22:01,629
Good morning.

218
00:22:01,840 --> 00:22:04,070
Are you in charge of...?

219
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:05,997
l’m Madame Ana'is.

220
00:22:06,320 --> 00:22:08,880
I came to see if —

221
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:11,719
Let’s go inside.
We’ll be more comfortable there.

222
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:20,912
Have a seat.
Can I offer you something?

223
00:22:21,040 --> 00:22:22,189
No, thanks.

224
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:24,794
- Cigarette?
- Thanks, I don’t smoke.

225
00:22:25,440 --> 00:22:28,477
Don’t be frightened.
Make yourself at home.

226
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:31,599
I’ll do whatever I can.
Sit down.

227
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:39,034
You’re nice, and fresh.
Just what they like here.

228
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:42,239
I know it’s hard at first,

229
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:45,238
but who doesn’t need money
now and then?

230
00:22:46,960 --> 00:22:49,349
We’ll split it fifty-fifty.

231
00:22:50,120 --> 00:22:51,917
l have my expenses.

232
00:22:52,040 --> 00:22:54,952
Thank you very much,
but I must be going.

233
00:22:56,120 --> 00:22:58,634
Come now.
You’re just a bit nervous.

234
00:23:01,080 --> 00:23:03,594
I bet it’s the first time
you’ve worked.

235
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:06,110
It’s not really so awful.

236
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:09,592
It’s still early.
The other girls aren’t here yet.

237
00:23:09,720 --> 00:23:11,756
You’re about to lose a button.

238
00:23:12,720 --> 00:23:14,631
When would you like to start?

239
00:23:14,760 --> 00:23:16,318
I don’t know.

240
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:17,714
Today?

241
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:20,638
Yes, perhaps.
But afternoons only.

242
00:23:20,760 --> 00:23:24,070
l have to leave at 5:00, without fail.

243
00:23:24,560 --> 00:23:26,039
All right,

244
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:29,516
but you must be punctual
or I’ll be very annoyed.

245
00:23:30,080 --> 00:23:32,674
I promise
you’ll be free to go at 5:00.

246
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:35,798
Good-bye, and excuse me.

247
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:38,639
l’ll expect you this afternoon at 2:00.

248
00:23:57,480 --> 00:23:59,232
What’s the matter?
Anything serious?

249
00:23:59,360 --> 00:24:01,749
No, l was out shopping

250
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:03,951
and just suddenly wanted
to see you.

251
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:07,390
- I thought you didn’t like hospitals.
- No, I don’t.

252
00:24:07,680 --> 00:24:10,797
I don’t feel like being alone.
Let me take you out to lunch.

253
00:24:10,920 --> 00:24:14,390
I’m having lunch with the boss.
I told you this morning.

254
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:16,795
- That’s true, but —
- I’m sorry.

255
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:20,034
Don’t forget we’re going out
with the Févrets tonight.

256
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:24,439
