339
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:12,237
Sorry. If I’d known,
I’d have put it in the fridge.

340
00:30:12,360 --> 00:30:16,797
- You knew I was coming.
- But not that Belle de jour was.

341
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:21,152
To the person
I care most about — me!

342
00:30:21,280 --> 00:30:23,271
And to Belle de jour.

343
00:30:25,560 --> 00:30:27,437
Good, but a little warm.

344
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:32,231
Mathilde, | forgot.
I do have a present for you.

345
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:36,279
Here.
- What is it?

346
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:38,072
Open it and see.

347
00:30:46,560 --> 00:30:48,039
Thank you.

348
00:30:54,080 --> 00:30:56,833
He’s funny.
He always has some surprise.

349
00:30:57,040 --> 00:30:58,871
Here’s to fun!

350
00:30:59,040 --> 00:31:01,759
I love life!
I like people to have fun!

351
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:10,191
Well, Belle de jour?

352
00:31:10,880 --> 00:31:12,552
You in a bad mood?

353
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:16,238
What’s the matter?

354
00:31:22,960 --> 00:31:24,598
You’ll see.

355
00:31:25,560 --> 00:31:28,472
I’ll show you a good time, I promise.

356
