778
01:07:53,000 --> 01:07:55,833
I’d like to keep you till tonight,
but I can’t.

779
01:07:56,200 --> 01:07:58,156
I like you too, Marcel.

780
01:07:58,760 --> 01:08:01,228
Will you come back?
- Maybe.

781
01:08:02,080 --> 01:08:03,399
If you don’t have money —

782
01:08:03,600 --> 01:08:06,910
Money isn’t a problem.

783
01:08:07,840 --> 01:08:09,512
You frighten me.

784
01:08:38,280 --> 01:08:39,793
See? You’re bored.

785
01:08:39,960 --> 01:08:43,396
I’m not.
I’d just like to get back to Paris.

786
01:08:43,960 --> 01:08:46,155
You can tell me absolutely anything,

787
01:08:46,280 --> 01:08:48,191
but you’re hiding something.

788
01:08:49,720 --> 01:08:52,996
If you tell me what’s bothering you,
maybe I can help.

789
01:08:53,120 --> 01:08:54,758
Tell you what?

790
01:08:55,520 --> 01:08:57,317
That you love someone.

791
01:08:57,440 --> 01:08:59,510
- Someone besides you?
- Yes.

792
01:08:59,880 --> 01:09:01,916
You know that’s impossible.

793
01:09:02,880 --> 01:09:07,351
I suggested this little vacation to see
if anything was tying you to Paris.

794
01:09:07,600 --> 01:09:09,795
l was right.
You want to go back.

795
01:09:10,480 --> 01:09:14,314
You’re always so distant.

796
01:09:15,120 --> 01:09:17,714
I’ve never felt you
really close to me.

797
01:09:17,880 --> 01:09:19,632
I’m sorry.

798
01:09:20,480 --> 01:09:22,277
I suppose it’s my fault.

799
01:09:22,480 --> 01:09:24,789
Does that prove I don’t love you?

800
01:09:24,920 --> 01:09:26,751
I think so.

801
01:09:32,120 --> 01:09:34,156
