816
01:10:30,120 --> 01:10:31,678
How’s it going?

817
01:10:37,240 --> 01:10:39,515
We waited for you on Thursday.

818
01:10:40,120 --> 01:10:43,237
- So?
- So next time we won’t wait.

819
01:10:43,600 --> 01:10:46,592
- We almost didn’t come today either.
- Really?

820
01:10:47,120 --> 01:10:49,031
Your cut keeps going up.

821
01:10:49,160 --> 01:10:51,469
We’re getting sick of you
and your little thug.

822
01:10:52,120 --> 01:10:55,510
Don’t fight with these punks.
Settle down.

823
01:10:55,640 --> 01:10:59,553
Gentlemen, if you have
something to settle, go outside.

824
01:10:59,680 --> 01:11:01,716
Shut your trap, you.

825
01:11:02,960 --> 01:11:05,758
The snow.
We know you’ve got it.

826
01:11:12,360 --> 01:11:14,396
Now don’t let us keep you.

827
01:11:17,160 --> 01:11:19,799
We’ll discuss that “thug” remark
some other time.

828
01:11:19,960 --> 01:11:21,518
As you like.

829
01:11:51,400 --> 01:11:53,789
Pierrot, another bottle.

830
01:12:03,720 --> 01:12:05,790
- Where you going?
- To make a call.

831
01:12:05,920 --> 01:12:07,319
Again?

832
01:12:11,120 --> 01:12:13,793
Broads... what a curse!

833
01:12:13,920 --> 01:12:17,356
You can say that again.
He’s got it bad.

834
01:12:17,520 --> 01:12:19,590
lt’s cost him dearly before.

835
01:12:19,720 --> 01:12:23,190
But it’s always been his weakness.
Nothing I can do.

836
01:12:23,880 --> 01:12:26,348
Ana'l's? lt’s Marcel.

837
01:12:26,840 --> 01:12:28,398
Any news?

838
01:12:29,960 --> 01:12:31,518
When?

839
01:12:31,840 --> 01:12:33,353
Really?

840
01:12:35,400 --> 01:12:37,152
I’ll be right there.

841
01:12:44,360 --> 01:12:47,989
“Carried his father on his back.”
Six letters.

842
01:12:48,880 --> 01:12:51,155
The third letter’s an N.

843
01:12:52,000 --> 01:12:54,753
“Aeneas,” with A-E at the start.

844
01:12:54,880 --> 01:12:58,316
Ah, right.
That comes up a lot in crosswords.

845
01:13:00,200 --> 01:13:03,192
Belle, it’s him again.
He’s waiting.

846
01:13:14,480 --> 01:13:16,710
Hello. How are you?

847
01:13:23,200 --> 01:13:26,078
Where were you?
Why did you go away?

848
01:13:26,400 --> 01:13:29,836
I had to leave Paris for a few days.
I can explain.

849
01:13:29,960 --> 01:13:33,953
I’ll explain a few things too,
and I’ll leave my signature as well.

850
01:13:44,600 --> 01:13:46,238
Don’t touch me!

851
01:13:47,080 --> 01:13:49,913
Do that once more
and you’ll never see me again.

852
01:13:52,960 --> 01:13:54,791
All right... this time.

853
01:14:20,200 --> 01:14:22,111
I missed you, you know.

854
01:14:23,280 --> 01:14:26,078
I shouldn’t tell you this,
but I waited for you.

855
01:14:26,640 --> 01:14:29,996
I want to see you more often now.
At night too.

856
01:14:30,120 --> 01:14:32,634
I’m here every day.
Isn’t that enough?

857
01:14:33,320 --> 01:14:35,834
You know I’m not free.
- I don’t give a damn.

858
01:14:49,480 --> 01:14:51,277
I don’t get it.

859
01:14:52,360 --> 01:14:54,351
You seem to like being with me.

860
01:14:54,480 --> 01:14:56,072
Very much...

861
01:14:56,200 --> 01:14:58,156
but it’s not enough.

862
01:14:58,320 --> 01:15:00,311
You love the other guy?

863
01:15:01,840 --> 01:15:03,717
Then why are you here?

864
01:15:03,840 --> 01:15:05,319
I don’t know.

865
01:15:05,440 --> 01:15:07,510
They’re two different things.

866
01:15:32,200 --> 01:15:34,191
l’m starving.
Where should we eat?

867
01:15:34,320 --> 01:15:36,356
No idea.
We’ll decide on the way.

868
01:15:36,480 --> 01:15:39,119
I’ll be back at 3:00.

869
01:15:40,560 --> 01:15:43,154
You’ve changed so much.
I hardly recognize you.

870
01:15:43,280 --> 01:15:46,670
It’s so nice to see you smile.
- I do feel much better.

871
01:15:46,800 --> 01:15:49,519
I’ve never seen you like this.
If only —

872
01:15:49,640 --> 01:15:50,675
What?

873
01:15:50,800 --> 01:15:54,110
If only one day you had
some great news for me.

874
01:15:54,240 --> 01:15:56,913
- What do you mean?
- You know very well.

875
01:15:57,040 --> 01:15:59,759
What I want
more than anything: a child.

876
01:16:15,840 --> 01:16:18,149
- What are you looking at?
- Nothing.

877
01:16:19,320 --> 01:16:22,869
This old thing caught my eye.
I don’t know why. It’s strange.

878
01:16:23,000 --> 01:16:26,197
- Nothing strange about it.
- No, you’re right.

879
01:16:34,160 --> 01:16:37,436
You’re back!
I didn’t recognize you.

880
01:16:37,560 --> 01:16:41,599
Did you forget about us,
you ungrateful devil? It’s been ages.

881
01:16:42,040 --> 01:16:44,235
But you haven’t changed.

882
01:16:44,440 --> 01:16:46,271
First door on the right.

883
01:16:50,360 --> 01:16:53,750
Come on, girls.
An old friend is back.

884
01:16:54,680 --> 01:16:58,593
Well? Let’s go!

885
01:17:03,280 --> 01:17:06,033
Yes, yes, you look lovely.

886
01:17:07,640 --> 01:17:11,792
- You’re flattering me.
- No, sir, I remember you well.

887
01:17:11,960 --> 01:17:14,952
I even dream about you sometimes.

888
01:17:16,080 --> 01:17:18,036
I don’t like the sound of that.

889
01:17:18,160 --> 01:17:21,835
- No, I couldn’t.
- I insist. Do me the pleasure.

890
01:17:25,680 --> 01:17:28,274
Hello, ladies. Sit down.
- Thanks.

891
01:17:28,400 --> 01:17:31,790
This is Mathilde,
Charlotte, and Belle de jour.

892
01:17:32,120 --> 01:17:35,157
Belle de jour? That’s original.

893
01:17:36,680 --> 01:17:38,830
Perhaps you’d like some refreshment.

894
01:17:39,320 --> 01:17:41,151
Later.

895
01:17:42,320 --> 01:17:44,117
Nothing’s changed here.

896
01:17:44,240 --> 01:17:46,754
Still the same homey welcome...

897
01:17:47,480 --> 01:17:49,152
the same drapes.

898
01:17:50,480 --> 01:17:53,597
Whatever happened to that girl,
the lion tamer?

899
01:17:55,000 --> 01:17:56,672
I haven’t heard from her.

900
01:17:56,800 --> 01:18:00,588
- And the heat’s up all the way?
- You haven’t changed either.

901
01:18:00,720 --> 01:18:02,836
Look, that armchair.

902
01:18:05,000 --> 01:18:06,513
It was snowing...

903
01:18:07,320 --> 01:18:09,515
The same special fragrance
in the air.

904
01:18:09,680 --> 01:18:11,432
Still jasmine.

905
01:18:12,080 --> 01:18:14,548
I hope you have some time for us.

906
01:18:14,680 --> 01:18:17,194
All my life.
I’m a man of leisure.

907
01:18:18,200 --> 01:18:19,474
Now, then...

908
01:18:19,600 --> 01:18:21,989
I’d like to be alone with Belle de jour.

909
01:18:27,840 --> 01:18:29,796
No, I won’t!

910
01:18:29,920 --> 01:18:32,878
Is this any way to behave?
You’ll stay.

911
01:18:36,040 --> 01:18:37,871
She’s very sweet.

912
01:18:39,200 --> 01:18:41,191
Just a little on edge sometimes.

913
01:18:44,880 --> 01:18:46,393
Happy now?

914
01:18:46,880 --> 01:18:49,519
Don’t tell me it’s coincidence.
You knew I was here.

915
01:18:49,640 --> 01:18:51,153
You’re wrong.

916
01:18:51,320 --> 01:18:54,073
It’s your fault.
You gave me this address.

917
01:18:54,840 --> 01:18:57,513
- You’re wrong.
- Come closer and I’ll scream!

918
01:18:57,640 --> 01:18:59,551
l’ll jump out the window!

919
01:19:05,880 --> 01:19:07,108
Is this your bed?

920
01:19:07,240 --> 01:19:09,117
You disgust me.
I already told you that.

921
01:19:09,240 --> 01:19:12,357
Yes, it’s my bed!
What else do you want to know?

922
01:19:13,440 --> 01:19:15,396
You like being humiliated.

923
01:19:15,560 --> 01:19:17,073
I don’t.

924
01:19:18,520 --> 01:19:20,192
Don’t tell Pierre.

925
01:19:20,840 --> 01:19:23,912
Pierre?
I admire him more and more.

926
01:19:25,320 --> 01:19:27,356
Please don’t tell him.

927
01:19:27,880 --> 01:19:30,155
At least try to understand.

928
01:19:30,280 --> 01:19:32,236
I’m lost.

929
01:19:32,360 --> 01:19:35,796
I can’t help it. I can’t fight it.

930
01:19:36,760 --> 01:19:40,070
I know I’ll have to atone
for everything one day.

931
01:19:40,680 --> 01:19:42,750
But I couldn’t live without it.

932
01:19:44,800 --> 01:19:47,109
Fine! Do as you like with me!

933
01:19:48,960 --> 01:19:50,916
No. Not now, anyway.

934
01:19:51,040 --> 01:19:55,397
I guess what attracted me
about you was your virtue.

935
01:19:55,560 --> 01:19:57,630
You were the wife of a boy scout.

936
01:19:57,760 --> 01:19:59,751
That’s all changed now.

937
01:19:59,880 --> 01:20:02,189
l have principles, unlike you.

938
01:20:02,480 --> 01:20:05,119
I won’t tell Pierre, of course.

939
01:20:06,480 --> 01:20:10,473
But I have friends I could tell.
I could send you some business.

940
01:20:11,480 --> 01:20:13,630
Sorry I don’t feel like it.

941
01:20:13,760 --> 01:20:15,751
It really doesn’t appeal at all.

942
01:20:16,880 --> 01:20:18,871
Another time, perhaps.

943
01:20:19,160 --> 01:20:20,639
Who knows?

944
01:20:20,760 --> 01:20:22,751
I won’t take up your time.

945
01:20:30,200 --> 01:20:33,636
This isn’t for you.
Get Pierre some chocolates for me.

946
01:20:33,760 --> 01:20:35,239
Good-bye.

947
01:21:23,160 --> 01:21:25,196
Ready? Go!

948
01:21:30,400 --> 01:21:31,879
Prepare!

949
01:21:32,400 --> 01:21:33,389
Fire!

950
01:22:12,440 --> 01:22:14,590
- He left already?
- Yes.

951
01:22:15,280 --> 01:22:16,952
May I speak with you?

952
01:22:18,280 --> 01:22:19,713
Run along.

953
01:22:27,160 --> 01:22:29,071
- l have to leave.
- When?

954
01:22:29,200 --> 01:22:30,474
Now.

955
01:22:30,600 --> 01:22:32,989
- But you’ll be back?
- Definitely not.

956
01:22:33,120 --> 01:22:34,599
Why?

957
01:22:35,160 --> 01:22:37,390
You could have told me sooner.

958
01:22:37,520 --> 01:22:41,399
Aren’t you happy here?
- Yes, fine. It’s just —

959
01:22:41,560 --> 01:22:43,118
Now I get it.

960
01:22:44,880 --> 01:22:46,359
lt’s Marcel.

961
01:22:47,360 --> 01:22:49,510
He was just here.
He was furious.

962
01:22:49,720 --> 01:22:51,950
Almost barged into your room.

963
01:22:52,680 --> 01:22:54,955
There’s something fishy there.

964
01:22:56,080 --> 01:22:57,911
Has he gotten demanding?

965
01:22:58,040 --> 01:23:02,477
Wants you to be his alone,
day and night?

966
01:23:03,640 --> 01:23:04,993
Yes.

967
01:23:05,800 --> 01:23:07,950
It’s always the same story with men.

968
01:23:09,400 --> 01:23:11,630
You’re right. You’d better go.

969
01:23:12,440 --> 01:23:15,034
There could be trouble one day.

970
01:23:16,120 --> 01:23:17,872
But I’ll miss you.

971
01:23:18,760 --> 01:23:20,478
Women like you...

972
01:23:21,480 --> 01:23:23,357
You and I got along well.

973
01:23:23,760 --> 01:23:25,079
It’s true.

974
01:23:25,200 --> 01:23:29,034
Let me know how you’re doing.
Call once in a while.

975
01:23:29,320 --> 01:23:30,992
I’d like that.

976
01:23:31,160 --> 01:23:33,196
Is there some address —
- No.

977
01:23:34,720 --> 01:23:36,995
Too bad.
What else can I say?

978
01:24:47,600 --> 01:24:50,068
Madame,
there’s a gentleman to see you.

979
01:24:50,200 --> 01:24:51,918
- Me?
- Yes.

980
01:24:52,120 --> 01:24:53,473
Who is it?
Do you know him?

981
01:24:53,600 --> 01:24:56,478
No, but he says it’s urgent.

982
01:25:01,600 --> 01:25:03,079
Hello.

983
01:25:06,000 --> 01:25:08,514
- Did you bring the catalog?
- Yes, madame.

984
01:25:08,640 --> 01:25:10,915
Sit down. Thank you, Maria.

985
01:25:12,960 --> 01:25:15,110
Not bad, the catalog thing.

986
01:25:17,680 --> 01:25:19,432
I like your little joint.

987
01:25:19,560 --> 01:25:21,869
What are you doing here?
You’re crazy! Go away!

988
01:25:22,000 --> 01:25:25,993
Since you weren’t at Ana'l's’s anymore,
I thought I’d pay you a visit,

989
01:25:26,120 --> 01:25:27,997
see how you’re doing.

990
01:25:28,880 --> 01:25:31,269
- How did you find me?
- Child’s play.

991
01:25:31,800 --> 01:25:33,631
Is this your husband?

992
01:25:33,800 --> 01:25:36,598
Good-looking guy.
A nice fellow.

993
01:25:37,040 --> 01:25:38,712
A lot better than me.

994
01:25:38,840 --> 01:25:41,035
- Please leave!
- Don’t worry.

995
01:25:41,160 --> 01:25:43,196
I won’t make a scene.

996
01:25:43,560 --> 01:25:46,028
I just want to know why you left.

997
01:25:46,200 --> 01:25:49,476
You hear me?
- Be quiet! The maid will hear.

998
01:25:49,680 --> 01:25:51,671
Go away. He’ll be home soon.

999
01:25:52,480 --> 01:25:55,119
I just got here
and you want me to leave?

1000
01:25:55,240 --> 01:25:57,117
- What do you want?
- To see you again.

1001
01:25:57,240 --> 01:26:00,118
Impossible.
I’m never going back there.

1002
01:26:05,160 --> 01:26:07,151
I’ll give you three days.

1003
01:26:07,280 --> 01:26:09,236
Find some excuse.

1004
01:26:09,480 --> 01:26:12,836
I’ll be waiting at the Hotel du Bois
on rue Fromentin.

1005
01:26:13,040 --> 01:26:16,316
You’ll spend the night with me.
- Impossible.

1006
01:26:21,360 --> 01:26:23,874
Very well. I’ll wait for him.

1007
01:26:26,320 --> 01:26:28,675
l have a lot to tell him.
- You wouldn’t dare.

1008
01:26:28,800 --> 01:26:30,199
Yes, I would.

1009
01:26:30,360 --> 01:26:33,830
I didn’t want it to come to this,
but since you’re forcing me —

1010
01:26:34,040 --> 01:26:36,235
I guess it’s just as well.

1011
01:26:36,840 --> 01:26:39,718
l’d decided to tell him anyway.
- Really?

1012
01:26:39,880 --> 01:26:42,030
He’d have found out
sooner or later.

1013
01:26:42,200 --> 01:26:44,509
One of our friends
discovered I was there.

1014
01:26:44,760 --> 01:26:47,069
I want to get it all off my chest.

1015
01:26:48,840 --> 01:26:51,149
Fine. We’ll both wait for him

1016
01:26:51,280 --> 01:26:55,114
and tell him together.
I don’t mind.

1017
01:27:04,520 --> 01:27:07,956
I’m begging you: Leave!
He’ll be home soon.

1018
01:27:21,400 --> 01:27:22,913
Don’t worry.

1019
01:27:23,640 --> 01:27:25,278
I’ll leave.

1020
01:27:26,200 --> 01:27:29,192
I didn’t believe you,
but I’m starting to understand.

1021
01:27:33,920 --> 01:27:35,911
Here’s the obstacle.

1022
01:27:44,520 --> 01:27:47,273
See you soon... Séverine.

1023
01:28:23,160 --> 01:28:26,311
- Did you see her?
- Yes. Let me have the car.

1024
01:28:26,680 --> 01:28:28,875
- Where are you going?
- I need it.

1025
01:28:29,480 --> 01:28:31,948
Let me have the car, and beat it.

1026
01:28:32,440 --> 01:28:34,476
What are you up to now?

1027
01:28:35,720 --> 01:28:37,392
I said beat it.

1028
01:28:38,120 --> 01:28:41,635
This time you’ve seen
the last of me, kid.

1029
01:30:05,800 --> 01:30:08,633
Oh no, you don’t!
You’re not running off!

1030
01:30:58,960 --> 01:30:59,949
Any news?

1031
01:31:00,080 --> 01:31:02,389
The killer’s dead,
and the police are baffled.

1032
01:31:02,560 --> 01:31:05,120
Either he shot the wrong guy
or he was crazy.

1033
01:31:05,240 --> 01:31:07,276
- Has he been identified?
- Yeah, a common crook.

1034
01:31:07,480 --> 01:31:10,278
It wasn’t his first murder.
- Strange.

1035
01:31:10,480 --> 01:31:12,789
- How’s Sérizy?
- Too early to say.

1036
01:31:12,920 --> 01:31:14,911
His wife’s in the waiting room.

1037
01:31:36,400 --> 01:31:37,879
How is he?

1038
01:31:38,000 --> 01:31:41,310
It’s too early to say,
but he’ll live, so try to relax.

1039
01:31:41,480 --> 01:31:44,472
- Can I see him?
- No, he’s still in a coma.

1040
01:31:44,640 --> 01:31:45,868
Perhaps tomorrow.

1041
01:31:46,000 --> 01:31:49,310
You should go home and try to rest.

1042
01:31:49,520 --> 01:31:52,637
We’ll give you an hourly report,
I promise.

1043
01:31:52,760 --> 01:31:54,239
Thank you.

1044
01:31:54,440 --> 01:31:55,998
Don’t worry.

1045
01:32:00,080 --> 01:32:02,389
Come on. I’ll see you home.

1046
01:33:11,080 --> 01:33:13,275
I sent Maria for the newspapers.

1047
01:33:13,760 --> 01:33:16,797
I know the articles you like.
I’ll read them to you.

1048
01:33:18,760 --> 01:33:22,389
Maria’s very nice,
and she’s so fond of you.

1049
01:33:25,760 --> 01:33:27,796
Everyone’s asking about you.

1050
01:33:30,280 --> 01:33:33,909
You’re getting better, you know.
The doctor’s very optimistic.

1051
01:33:34,800 --> 01:33:37,712
You don’t realize it,
but you’ve made great progress.

1052
01:33:37,880 --> 01:33:39,632
Your eyes especially.

1053
01:33:41,200 --> 01:33:43,509
It’s funny.
Ever since you were —

1054
01:33:43,680 --> 01:33:47,150
Ever since your accident,
my dreams have stopped.

1055
01:33:48,880 --> 01:33:51,713
I think it’s time for your drops.

1056
01:34:18,320 --> 01:34:21,517
Mr. Husson, madame.
He’d //ke to see your husband

1057
01:34:27,280 --> 01:34:28,793
I’m coming.

1058
01:34:39,920 --> 01:34:41,478
Hello, Séverine.

1059
01:34:41,600 --> 01:34:43,511
I’m sorry to bother you.

1060
01:34:43,840 --> 01:34:45,671
You want to see Pierre?

1061
01:34:45,800 --> 01:34:47,472
Just for a moment.

1062
01:34:47,920 --> 01:34:50,514
You know, he still can’t speak.

1063
01:34:50,960 --> 01:34:52,632
I know.

1064
01:34:52,760 --> 01:34:54,671
I’m sorry I couldn’t come sooner.

1065
01:34:54,800 --> 01:34:57,678
You know how I admire Pierre,
but I was out of town.

1066
01:34:58,120 --> 01:34:59,997
Pretty dress.

1067
01:35:00,840 --> 01:35:03,593
You look like
a precocious schoolgirl.

1068
01:35:05,240 --> 01:35:08,232
- What do you want to tell Pierre?
- Everything I know about you.

1069
01:35:08,360 --> 01:35:09,429
What?

1070
01:35:09,560 --> 01:35:11,118
Calm down.

1071
01:35:12,240 --> 01:35:16,313
He’s paralyzed now,
completely dependent on you.

1072
01:35:18,200 --> 01:35:21,715
He’s ashamed of being a burden
on such a virtuous wife,

1073
01:35:21,840 --> 01:35:24,832
so I’ve decided
to tell him everything.

1074
01:35:25,680 --> 01:35:29,036
He’ll be hurt, but I think
I’ll be doing him a favor.

1075
01:35:31,680 --> 01:35:34,513
Who could call me cruel after that?

1076
01:35:37,400 --> 01:35:39,152
Take me to him, please.

1077
01:35:41,760 --> 01:35:43,273
He’s in there.

1078
01:35:48,880 --> 01:35:51,872
Would you like to be present
for our conversation?

1079
01:38:20,120 --> 01:38:22,509
What are you
thinking about, Séverine?

1080
01:38:24,160 --> 01:38:26,390
l was thinking about you.

1081
01:38:26,760 --> 01:38:28,273
l’m thirsty.

1082
01:38:47,760 --> 01:38:50,957
- Shall I ask for some ice?
- No, don’t bother.

1083
01:38:52,880 --> 01:38:55,758
I can get two weeks off
this February.

1084
01:38:55,880 --> 01:38:58,394
- Shall we go to the mountains?
- If you’d like.

1085
01:39:11,280 --> 01:39:12,998
Do you hear that?

